1
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:37,799
- So, Betsy, why am I doing this?
- You're tired, stressed,

2
00:01:37,924 --> 00:01:42,720
and they'll carry you out of the office
on a stretcher if you don't get some rest.

3
00:01:42,845 --> 00:01:46,516
- Duncan can take care of things.
- Duncan? Are you kidding me?

4
00:01:46,641 --> 00:01:51,646
He is your partner. And believe it or not,
he is just as worried about you as I am.

5
00:01:51,771 --> 00:01:56,776
Go. It's a vacation. You're late already.
I won't let you put this off this time.

6
00:01:56,901 --> 00:01:59,612
OK, OK, I'm not gonna put it off.

7
00:01:59,737 --> 00:02:03,032
But I am taking those plans.
They're not good enough.

8
00:02:03,157 --> 00:02:06,619
Now, how do you know that this spa
is any good anyway?

9
00:02:06,744 --> 00:02:08,788
Fine. I-l'm fine.

10
00:02:09,622 --> 00:02:13,751
- Don't forget to exercise.
- Exercise? Exercise is not rest.

11
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:18,381
- Sure you know where you're going?
- Yes. I'm very good with directions.

12
00:02:18,506 --> 00:02:21,592
Betsy, I'm completely lost. I'm sorry.

13
00:02:23,469 --> 00:02:25,513
I thought I was on 128,

14
00:02:25,638 --> 00:02:29,726
but I'm in the middle of the woods,
and, uh, I don't like it.

15
00:02:32,019 --> 00:02:34,105
Yeah. Hang on a second.

16
00:02:34,647 --> 00:02:37,150
OK, wait. I've got... I've got the map.

17
00:02:37,275 --> 00:02:41,696
I've got the map here. You know what?
There's... there's no Bear Mountain.

18
00:02:41,821 --> 00:02:44,574
There's no sign. I've been looking for it.

19
00:02:44,699 --> 00:02:47,326
Yeah, I did. I... I...

20
00:02:47,452 --> 00:02:50,163
Oh! Wow, wait. There's the sign. I got it.

21
00:02:50,288 --> 00:02:53,249
All right. I'll see you in a week.

22
00:02:53,374 --> 00:02:55,418
OK, thanks. Bye.

23
00:03:08,931 --> 00:03:12,977
Your room's in the Timber Lodge,
which is to the left.

24
00:03:13,603 --> 00:03:18,024
In the main lodge, we have a full
weight room, Lifecycles, step machines,

25
00:03:18,149 --> 00:03:22,153
spa, yoga, aerobics, cycling workouts.

26
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:25,239
I was really hoping for, like, a quick fix.

27
00:03:25,364 --> 00:03:28,868
Uh, do you have anything
that involves just lying down?

28
00:03:29,494 --> 00:03:32,038
- A massage?
- Yeah.

29
00:03:32,538 --> 00:03:35,625
Um, I'll have one a day, and not too early.

30
00:03:36,459 --> 00:03:38,169
How's 10am?

31
00:03:38,294 --> 00:03:39,837
Eleven?

32
00:03:39,962 --> 00:03:42,423
- Thank you. Good night.
- Good night.

33
00:03:44,967 --> 00:03:47,011
Oh!

34
00:03:47,970 --> 00:03:49,931
Virgil! Oh!

35
00:03:50,056 --> 00:03:52,016
God! There... Oh!

36
00:03:52,141 --> 00:03:54,727
No, no, no, no. Harder. Just right...

37
00:03:54,852 --> 00:03:55,895
Oh!

38
00:03:56,020 --> 00:04:00,358
No, you can't stop. Just a little more...

39
00:04:00,483 --> 00:04:02,860
- Come on, time's up.
- No, no... Oh!

40
00:04:05,655 --> 00:04:08,116
Virgil, you have to come live with me.

41
00:04:08,241 --> 00:04:10,827
What would your husband say?

42
00:04:10,952 --> 00:04:13,496
- I'll see you.
- Oh...

43
00:04:13,621 --> 00:04:16,582
That's it. I'm getting a divorce!

44
00:04:18,710 --> 00:04:21,337
- Amy, are you out there?
- Yeah?

45
00:04:21,462 --> 00:04:23,506
Come on in.

46
00:04:29,220 --> 00:04:31,180
- Hi, I'm Virgil.
- Hi.

47
00:04:31,305 --> 00:04:35,184
Take your clothes off
and hop up on the table. I'll be right there.

48
00:04:35,309 --> 00:04:37,270
You sound like a genius at this.

49
00:04:37,395 --> 00:04:41,858
Oh, yeah, Einstein, Gandhi...
Virgil Adamson, massage therapist.

50
00:04:43,776 --> 00:04:47,947
Do you want me...
sunny-side up or down?

51
00:04:48,781 --> 00:04:51,701
Mm, on your stomach, I think.

52
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:57,373
I'm gonna start off... somewhat deep.

53
00:04:59,167 --> 00:05:03,796
And, uh, you let me know
if you want anything deeper.

54
00:05:03,921 --> 00:05:05,089
Deeper is good.

55
00:05:05,214 --> 00:05:07,759
Where I come from, all you get is shallow.

56
00:05:07,925 --> 00:05:10,720
Ah! A New Yorker.

57
00:05:13,556 --> 00:05:15,600
Now, how do you know that?

58
00:05:15,725 --> 00:05:18,102
Oh, it's all here in the shoulders.

59
00:05:19,312 --> 00:05:23,775
Here's that honking horn
of the taxi you missed.

60
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:26,611
Here's the... rumble of the subway.

61
00:05:26,736 --> 00:05:29,822
Right in here is the screech of the wheels

62
00:05:29,947 --> 00:05:33,326
cos you're late,
and that's why you have that tension.

63
00:05:33,451 --> 00:05:36,204
You... get into the city very often?

64
00:05:36,329 --> 00:05:41,084
Do you want to talk or a... massage?

65
00:05:41,209 --> 00:05:43,878
Shutting up now.

66
00:05:54,764 --> 00:05:56,391
Mm-mm.

67
00:06:03,773 --> 00:06:05,817
Mm...

68
00:06:12,198 --> 00:06:14,742
That too deep?

69
00:06:14,867 --> 00:06:18,663
No, um... It's... fine.

70
00:06:20,832 --> 00:06:22,959
Oh, it is too deep.

71
00:06:24,168 --> 00:06:26,838
Maybe we should stop for today.

72
00:06:26,963 --> 00:06:29,799
Here's a Kleenex.

73
00:06:29,924 --> 00:06:33,219
I don't... I don't know why I'm crying.

74
00:06:37,598 --> 00:06:41,060
There must've been a lot of stuff built up.
I'm sorry.

75
00:06:41,185 --> 00:06:42,562
Sure.

76
00:06:43,646 --> 00:06:47,650
I'm gonna go now,
unless you'd like me to stay.

77
00:06:47,775 --> 00:06:49,736
Could you, please?

78
00:06:49,861 --> 00:06:52,697
Oh, sure... Sure.

79
00:07:00,246 --> 00:07:02,915
Do you always make the girls cry?

80
00:07:03,041 --> 00:07:04,333
Always.

81
00:07:05,668 --> 00:07:07,003
Just relax.

82
00:07:07,128 --> 00:07:08,129
OK.

83
00:08:16,948 --> 00:08:18,282
Hey, Virgil.

84
00:08:18,408 --> 00:08:20,618
- Virgil!
- Caroline! You look good.

85
00:08:20,743 --> 00:08:24,747
Oh, thank you. What a compliment!
See you tomorrow.

86
00:08:27,291 --> 00:08:28,543
Hey, Virgil!

87
00:08:29,752 --> 00:08:32,797
Can I take your bag?
I'll meet you in the lobby.

88
00:08:32,922 --> 00:08:36,342
Hey! Virgil!

89
00:08:37,427 --> 00:08:39,554
- Hi!
- Hi.

90
00:08:39,679 --> 00:08:41,347
It's... Amy...

91
00:08:41,472 --> 00:08:43,516
- Amy Benic.
- Oh. Yeah.

92
00:08:43,641 --> 00:08:45,518
I didn't recognise you
with your clothes on.

93
00:08:46,686 --> 00:08:50,398
You fell asleep,
so I thought it best if I just left.

94
00:08:50,523 --> 00:08:52,567
Oh, thank you.

95
00:08:53,401 --> 00:08:57,280
My God, you're the skater.
I saw you... Iast night driving in.

96
00:08:57,405 --> 00:08:58,406
Really?

97
00:08:58,531 --> 00:09:01,576
Yeah! You're good with that stick.
Are you on a team?

98
00:09:01,701 --> 00:09:04,328
Are you a hockey fan?

99
00:09:04,454 --> 00:09:08,458
I don't know. I don't really know
much about it, but it looks like fun.

100
00:09:08,583 --> 00:09:11,294
I skated as a kid,
but I've got two left feet.

101
00:09:13,504 --> 00:09:15,506
Well, this is my ride.

102
00:09:17,592 --> 00:09:18,593
Tommy?

103
00:09:19,260 --> 00:09:21,554
Hey, Virge.

104
00:09:23,556 --> 00:09:27,185
I just wanted to apologise
for falling apart like that.

105
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:30,521
Um, I was just in a weird place. Sorry.

106
00:09:30,646 --> 00:09:33,983
- And now?
- Now I'm feeling good.

107
00:09:34,108 --> 00:09:36,277
So I wanted to thank you.

108
00:09:36,402 --> 00:09:40,573
- For making you cry?
- No. I made me cry.

109
00:09:40,698 --> 00:09:43,284
But you were very kind to me. Thank you.

110
00:09:43,409 --> 00:09:45,953
Virgil! Virgil, let's move it.

111
00:09:46,079 --> 00:09:49,290
I'm gonna see you tomorrow.
I booked another massage.

112
00:09:49,415 --> 00:09:52,210
- OK. I'll see you tomorrow.
- Nice to see you.

113
00:09:52,335 --> 00:09:55,004
OK. All right.

114
00:09:57,173 --> 00:09:59,217
See you.

115
00:09:59,634 --> 00:10:00,760
Oh, my God.

116
00:10:02,011 --> 00:10:03,971
What?

117
00:10:04,097 --> 00:10:06,974
I'm sorry. I didn't... realise...

118
00:10:07,809 --> 00:10:08,893
Wow.

119
00:10:09,018 --> 00:10:12,146
- Hey, you already apologised once.
- Oh, God.

120
00:10:12,271 --> 00:10:16,776
- No need to overdo it.
- OK. I'll see you tomorrow.

121
00:10:16,901 --> 00:10:18,861
See you tomorrow.

122
00:10:18,986 --> 00:10:20,071
Bye.

123
00:10:55,356 --> 00:10:57,567
Jessie, get off the bed.

124
00:11:00,111 --> 00:11:03,531
There you are. Come here, boy.

125
00:11:03,656 --> 00:11:07,452
You're more like a sleeping-eye dog
than a Seeing Eye dog.

126
00:11:07,577 --> 00:11:11,748
Come here, you. Come on.

127
00:11:11,873 --> 00:11:14,292
There's a game on.

128
00:11:14,417 --> 00:11:16,461
Come on.

129
00:11:16,961 --> 00:11:20,506
Hey, I met a girl today.

130
00:11:20,631 --> 00:11:24,844
- She had an amazing voice. It was
- A charade sheet. OK!

131
00:11:24,969 --> 00:11:27,597
smooth like butter.

132
00:11:27,722 --> 00:11:31,601
And she smelled like...
cinnamon and nutmeg.

133
00:11:31,726 --> 00:11:35,438
Sounds more like a recipe
for a coffee cake than a girl.

134
00:11:35,938 --> 00:11:39,442
You're here! I didn't hear you.

135
00:11:40,234 --> 00:11:44,447
As this game starts, Sundstrom
goes for the puck. Winds it around.

136
00:11:44,572 --> 00:11:47,533
- So, how are the kids?
- Oh, the usual.

137
00:11:47,658 --> 00:11:50,036
They need a lot of attention. Here.

138
00:11:52,455 --> 00:11:56,125
- So, who's the girl?
- Oh, just a spa girl. Client.

139
00:11:57,627 --> 00:11:59,629
Gone in a week.

140
00:11:59,754 --> 00:12:04,509
Look, if you like coffee cake that much,
we can sprinkle cinnamon on Jessie.

141
00:12:04,634 --> 00:12:08,137
- Too old for me.
- Who? Jessie or the girl?

142
00:12:08,262 --> 00:12:10,556
Not jealous of a coffee cake, are you?

143
00:12:11,557 --> 00:12:14,185
- Coke?
- I'm fine.

144
00:12:14,310 --> 00:12:16,270
Your lunch is ready.

145
00:12:16,396 --> 00:12:21,109
- Chicken's at 3 o'clock.
- Rice is at 6 o'clock. Beans are at 9,...

146
00:12:21,234 --> 00:12:24,654
- ..and the news is at 1 1 .
- One day, I'm gonna switch 'em.

147
00:12:24,779 --> 00:12:29,283
Yeah. And one day I'll play forward
for the New York Rangers.

148
00:12:30,368 --> 00:12:33,413
- You need better jokes.
- Or a new sister.

149
00:12:33,538 --> 00:12:36,082
Mm, I'd work on the jokes if I were you.

150
00:12:37,291 --> 00:12:39,585
Aren't you gonna watch some hockey?

151
00:12:39,711 --> 00:12:43,631
You want to grade some spelling tests?
I'm next door if you need me.

152
00:12:43,756 --> 00:12:45,842
OK. Thanks a lot.

153
00:12:47,427 --> 00:12:49,470
So, this girl...

154
00:12:49,846 --> 00:12:52,640
We talked for a long time at the bus stop.

155
00:12:54,767 --> 00:12:56,811
She thought I could see.

156
00:13:00,481 --> 00:13:02,483
I really love coffee cake.

157
00:13:34,682 --> 00:13:38,186
Oh! Oh! Whoa! Oh!

158
00:13:38,311 --> 00:13:40,354
Oh, shoot.

159
00:13:44,317 --> 00:13:46,402
Coming, coming!

160
00:13:46,527 --> 00:13:49,280
Hang on! Hang on. OK.

161
00:13:51,657 --> 00:13:53,451
Coming!

162
00:13:55,161 --> 00:13:57,580
- Hi.
- Oh, my God. Hi.

163
00:13:57,705 --> 00:13:59,457
My turn to apologise.

164
00:13:59,582 --> 00:14:02,877
- I should have told you I was blind.
- Well,

165
00:14:03,503 --> 00:14:07,090
we're even.
Apologies cancel each other out.

166
00:14:07,215 --> 00:14:11,636
You wanna come in? Sorry. I just got out
of the shower. I have to change.

167
00:14:11,761 --> 00:14:13,805
Promise I won't look.

168
00:14:14,263 --> 00:14:16,307
Uh-huh!

169
00:14:18,643 --> 00:14:22,939
Uh... I sort of spilled
some stuff on the floor.

170
00:14:23,106 --> 00:14:28,361
Here, why don't you sit down on the bed?
I'm just gonna go change. Be right back.

171
00:14:29,237 --> 00:14:31,280
All right.

172
00:14:31,698 --> 00:14:35,451
You didn't have to come all the way
back up here just to apologise.

173
00:14:35,576 --> 00:14:39,372
- I was in the neighbourhood.
- You were in the neighbourhood?

174
00:14:39,497 --> 00:14:41,499
Oh, all right, I'll confess.

175
00:14:41,624 --> 00:14:47,338
I was watching hockey with my dog,
and, um... I was describing you.

176
00:14:47,463 --> 00:14:49,048
What?

177
00:14:49,173 --> 00:14:55,054
I was describing how great you smelled.
My sister thought I was describing a cake.

178
00:14:55,179 --> 00:14:57,598
Anyway, I started thinking of you here

179
00:14:57,724 --> 00:15:01,769
in the midst of your tofu shake
and really boring yoghurt.

180
00:15:01,894 --> 00:15:05,732
I thought maybe you'd want to
get some air, take a walk around town.

181
00:15:06,733 --> 00:15:10,486
- Just see what we see.
- See what we see?

182
00:15:10,611 --> 00:15:14,615
- Figure of speech.
- You mean, right here, right now?

183
00:15:15,408 --> 00:15:18,870
- Great! I'm blind and you're deaf.
- What a pair.

184
00:15:20,038 --> 00:15:21,914
52 lampposts... Pinecrest.

185
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:25,334
Up here on our left
is my sister Jennie's school.

186
00:15:26,169 --> 00:15:29,005
She's really great with these kids.

187
00:15:29,130 --> 00:15:31,758
You see that guy across the street?

188
00:15:31,883 --> 00:15:34,469
- Over in the doorway.
- Uh...

189
00:15:34,594 --> 00:15:37,180
- He's chain-smoking, right?
- Oh, yeah!

190
00:15:37,305 --> 00:15:41,392
That's Bruce. We watch
the game together sometimes.

191
00:15:42,935 --> 00:15:47,315
Here comes Nancy. She's the librarian.
Gets me any book I want in Braille.

192
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:51,110
- Hey, Nancy!
- Hey, Virgil! I got that book in for you.

193
00:15:51,235 --> 00:15:53,988
Still haven't got that old jalopy fixed.

194
00:15:54,113 --> 00:15:56,866
If I got it fixed,
how would you know it was me?

195
00:15:56,991 --> 00:15:57,950
Hi.

196
00:15:58,076 --> 00:16:01,996
- Nancy, this is Amy. Amy, Nancy.
- Hi, Amy. Nice to meet you.

197
00:16:02,121 --> 00:16:05,083
- Have fun.
- Be careful, honey. He's all hands.

198
00:16:05,208 --> 00:16:07,251
- Be nice.
- Yeah!

199
00:16:09,796 --> 00:16:13,800
Nice town you have here.
You're very popular with the ladies.

200
00:16:13,925 --> 00:16:16,928
Oh, yeah. Moved here when I was eight.

201
00:16:17,053 --> 00:16:20,098
They figured it was a good place
for me to grow up in.

202
00:16:20,223 --> 00:16:22,934
It's a bit geriatric, but... it works.

203
00:16:25,019 --> 00:16:28,064
Do you mind me asking
how long you've been blind?

204
00:16:28,189 --> 00:16:30,149
No, not at all.

205
00:16:30,274 --> 00:16:35,405
It started when I was one.
Completely gone by the time I was three.

206
00:16:35,530 --> 00:16:37,490
Congenital cataracts,

207
00:16:37,615 --> 00:16:41,828
with a dose of retinitis pigmentosa
thrown in for good measure.

208
00:16:41,953 --> 00:16:42,704
Huh.

209
00:16:42,829 --> 00:16:46,708
So... So, you see no bright lights?

210
00:16:46,833 --> 00:16:47,750
Nothing?

211
00:16:47,875 --> 00:16:49,836
Nope. Blind as a bat.

212
00:16:49,961 --> 00:16:54,632
Actually, blinder. Um, bats emit sonar.
I wish I had that sonar.

213
00:16:54,757 --> 00:16:57,719
I don't have a sixth sense. Or a fifth one.

214
00:16:57,844 --> 00:17:00,179
Never wrote a book like Helen Keller.

215
00:17:00,304 --> 00:17:02,849
Wish I could play the piano
like Ray Charles.

216
00:17:02,974 --> 00:17:06,686
I really wish I could sing
like Stevie Wonder. But I can't.

217
00:17:06,811 --> 00:17:09,814
Got it. Huh.

218
00:17:12,233 --> 00:17:18,156
So, what do you, uh, think,
of our, uh, little Sleepy Hollow?

219
00:17:19,032 --> 00:17:23,202
It has a very nice feel to it.
Genuine lines, good use of space.

220
00:17:23,327 --> 00:17:28,207
I'd do something more stimulating with
the newer buildings, but that's just me.

221
00:17:28,332 --> 00:17:29,959
Wow!

222
00:17:30,209 --> 00:17:33,838
What's you?
Are you a writer for Architectural Digest?

223
00:17:33,963 --> 00:17:36,424
Um, no, I'm actually an architect.

224
00:17:36,549 --> 00:17:39,552
That's what I do.
I have a partnership in New York.

225
00:17:39,677 --> 00:17:41,471
- Really?
- Yeah.

226
00:17:41,596 --> 00:17:43,056
Wow.

227
00:17:44,474 --> 00:17:46,517
Well...

228
00:17:47,018 --> 00:17:49,020
This is the end.

229
00:17:49,145 --> 00:17:51,105
Guess we should go back.

230
00:17:51,230 --> 00:17:54,692
Well, what's out there,
past the end of the street?

231
00:17:55,777 --> 00:17:57,820
Nothing.

232
00:17:59,781 --> 00:18:03,826
Well, there is a, um,
old run-down building off to the left.

233
00:18:03,951 --> 00:18:06,496
Kind of like an old gas station.

234
00:18:08,539 --> 00:18:10,583
Would you describe it to me?

235
00:18:10,958 --> 00:18:12,752
OK.

236
00:18:12,877 --> 00:18:15,922
Um... It's kind of dilapidated

237
00:18:16,047 --> 00:18:20,718
and it's sitting in between
two great big trees in a field.

238
00:18:20,843 --> 00:18:25,348
The trees are like a man and a woman.
The man is asking the woman to dance.

239
00:18:25,473 --> 00:18:29,727
And the woman is... on her toes,
trying to decide if she's got the guts.

240
00:18:31,396 --> 00:18:34,690
Oh, God, I'm an idiot.
What a stupid description!

241
00:18:34,816 --> 00:18:36,609
No.

242
00:18:37,318 --> 00:18:40,154
I really like the... dancing trees.

243
00:18:43,950 --> 00:18:46,869
We better get going. It's starting to rain.

244
